                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " I really enjoyed this set of articles.  Here are some of the quotes that resonate strongly for me:\nFrom article 1:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "CPUs and memory are now effectively free. The original justification evaporated. What remained was the notation, now mistaken for ground truth."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "From article 2:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Every notation has a sweet spot — a class of problems it expresses clearly and cheaply. Outside that sweet spot, the notation fights you."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "From article 3:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Every one of these domains is stateful by nature. The state does not go away because the notation ignores it."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "-\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Hidden state is not safe state. It is state that is harder to reason about, harder to test, and harder to modify."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "From article 4:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "The question is not “can this notation express the problem?” The question is “does this notation make the problem easy to express, easy to reason about, easy to modify, and easy to communicate?”"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "From article 5:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "A GPL must be expressive enough to handle every problem domain, which means it cannot be optimally expressive for any particular one.\nLittle languages — small, purpose-built notations for specific problem domains — make the opposite trade."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "The mismatch between the dominant notation(s) and the things we really care about when designing software screams at me everyday."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
